/wiki/Jesmond_Zerafa: Jesmond Zerafa (born 3 August 1965 in Malta) is a former professional footballer. During his career, he played primarily as a striker.
Qormi Football Club is a Maltese football club from the city of Qormi, that currently plays in the Maltese Division one.
Valletta Football Club is a professional football club based in Valletta, the capital city of Malta, and competes in the Maltese Premier League, the top flight of Maltese football. The club was founded in 1943 after a merge of Valletta Prestons, Valletta St. Paul's and Valletta United, the latter being a two-time league winner before the Second World War.
/wiki/Jordi_Cruyff: Johan Jordi Cruijff (Dutch pronunciation: [ˈjoːɦɑn ˈjɔrdi krœyf], anglicised to Cruyff; born 9 February 1974) is a Dutch football coach and former player. Cruyff is the son of former player and manager Johan Cruyff. He is the head coach of the Ecuador national football team.
/wiki/AEK_Larnaca: AEK Larnaca FC (Greek: AEK; for short Αθλητική Έvωση Κίτιον Λάρνακας, romanized: Athletiki Enosi Kition Larnakas, "Athletic Union Kition of Larnaca") is a Cypriot professional football club from Larnaca, Cyprus. Their home ground as from the 2016–2017 season is the brand new AEK Arena - Georgios Karapatakis stadium with a capacity of 7,400 spectators. The club was formed in 1994 after a merger of two Larnaca clubs, EPA Larnaca and Pezoporikos. The club has also basketball sections for men AEK Larnaca BC and a volleyball section for women.
/wiki/Ton_Caanen: Ton Caanen (born March 18, 1966 in Geleen, Netherlands) is a Dutch football manager.
Dingli Swallows Football Club is a Maltese football club from the small village of Ħad-Dingli, which currently plays in the Maltese Third Division. The club was founded in 1948.
/wiki/Stephen_Azzopardi: Stephen Azzopardi (born 27 August 1967) is a Maltese football coach.
/wiki/Zoran_Popovic: Zoran Popović (Serbian Cyrillic: Зоран Поповић; born 28 May 1988) is a Serbian professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for Serbian club Red Star Belgrade.
Floriana Football Club is a Maltese football club in the town of Floriana that currently plays in the Maltese Premier League. In all, Floriana F.C. has won 25 national leagues  and 20 FA Trophies. It is also the only team from Malta to have qualified from the qualifying rounds to the first round proper of the UEFA Champions League, in the 1993–94 season.
Msida Saint Joseph Football Club – usually referred to as Msida St. Joseph – is a Maltese football club from the town of Msida, which currently plays in the Maltese First Division.
